      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. experimental (N=11)",
      "description": "FEA-predicted construct stiffness (N/mm) compared against pooled experimental measurements from Laboratory 1 (n=6) and Laboratory 2 (n=5). The normalized error metric E/uval was computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3. All 11 specimen comparisons yielded E/uval < 1.96, satisfying the pre-specified acceptance criterion. Mean FEA prediction deviated from experimental mean by 4.2%, within the <10% QoI bound. The ensemble spread across the three FEA implementations (FDA solver, Ansys Mechanical, DePuy Synthes proprietary) was less than 1.5% for all specimens, confirming numerical consistency. Experimental uncertainty was characterized using Type A evaluation over replicate tests within each laboratory; inter-laboratory reproducibility was confirmed by an F-test at α=0.05. This result constitutes the primary quantitative evidence supporting model credibility for the stiffness quantity of interest. The testing campaign was conducted under ASTM F1717-15 protocol with polyaxial screws inserted at 5° convergence angle in UHMWPE blocks representing L4–L5 anatomy. Load application rate was 25 mm/min; load cell calibration traceable to NIST. The complete test records, including raw force-displacement curves, are archived in the dataset bindsDataset entry bench-test-lab1-n6 and bench-test-lab2-n5. FEA boundary conditions were matched to fixture geometry as documented in the model verification report. The narrative here fully characterizes the generation context for this result.",
